 Each State agency must enter into an agreement with FNS (Form
FNS-74, the Federal-State Agreement) prior to receiving commodities
or administrative funds;

 A statement that each agency receiving commodities for distribution
is responsible for any loss resulting from improper distribution, or
improper storage, care, or handling of commodities;

 A description of the specific functions that the State,
subdistributing, or local agency is delegating to another agency;
and

 Developing a plan for the detection and prevention of dual
participation, in coordination with CSFP local agencies and with the
State WIC agency;

 Developing a management review system and conducting reviews of
local agencies. (This function may not be delegated to another
agency.);

 A description of the standards the State agency will use in
determining if the pursuit of a claim against a participant is
cost-effective;

The Medicaid Program, which is the medical assistance program established under Title XIX of the Social Security Act (
